5rem;\"></strong></p></div><div><ol><li><strong><strong><strong>Makeup Theory Quiz-1 (Marks: 10) and Makeup Lab Quiz-1 (Marks: 5) will be held on 22/04/2026 (Wednesday) in offline mode.</strong></strong></strong></li><li><strong><strong><strong>All the absent students in the previous quiz must report for the Quiz at 12:50 PM sharp in LT101.</strong></strong></strong></li><li><strong><strong><strong>The quiz is of 20 minutes long and will commence sharp at 01:00 PM.</strong></strong></strong></li><li><strong><strong><strong>No further make-up Quiz is there.</strong></strong></strong></li><li><strong><strong><strong>One Question may contain more than one correct answer.</strong></strong><br></strong></li></ol><strong>Syllabus for Makeup Theory Quiz-1 is:</strong><p></p><p><strong></strong></p></div><div><b>Introduction to Microprocessors:</b>&nbsp;Generic Architecture of Microprocessor, Overview of 8085 microprocessor, Architecture, Instruction Set, Programming Examples.</div><div><br><b>INTEL 8086 Microprocessor:</b>&nbsp;Pin Functions, Architecture, Characteristics and Basic Features of Family, Segmented Memory, Interrupt Structures, INTEL 8086 System Configuration, Addressing Modes, Description of Instructions: Data Transfer and Arithmetic Instructions.<p></p><p></p></div><strong>Syllabus for <strong>Makeup&nbsp;</strong>Lab Quiz-1 is:<br></strong><br><strong><b>Introduction to INTEL kit, Programming examples of 8085 and 8086.</b></strong><span></span><span></span><br><p></p></div>","visible":1,"uservisible":true,"visibleoncoursepage":1,"modicon":"https://lms.thapar.edu/moodle/theme/image.php/moove/page/1659956381/icon","modname":"page","modplural":"Pages","indent":0,"onclick":"","afterlink":null,"customdata":"\"\"","noviewlink":false,"completion":1,"completiondata":{"state":0,"timecompleted":0,"overrideby":null,"valueused":false},"contents":[{"type":"file","filename":"Theory Quiz-1_Seating Plan (UCS617).pdf","filepath":"/","filesize":69211,"fileurl":"https://lms.t